-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-	-> This directory contains MATLAB code for the summer internship projet:	-
-	Mesure statistique de l'apparition de phénomènes de propagation anormale 	-
-	entre un émetteur constant et un récepteur basé à Rambouillet			-
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-	-> MATLAB version used:								-
-		- R2012b (8.0.0.783) 64-bit						-
-					 						-
-	-> Special toolboxes used: 							-
-		- Statistics Toolbox (Version 8.1)					-
-											-
-	-> Other dependencies:								-
-											-										-
-	- rotateXLabels.m								-
-		rotates all XLabels on axes AX by an angle				-
-		ANGLE (in degrees). Handles to the resulting text objects are returned	-
-		in HH.									-
-	CREATED BY: Ben Tordoff								-
-	Mathworks profile:								-
-	http://fr.mathworks.com/matlabcentral/profile/authors/1297191-ben-tordoff	-
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-	-> Main functions:								-
-											-
-	- readMeasures.m								-
-		Read data from a file generated by the LabView application		-
-											-
-	- readData.m									-
-		Read data from multiples files generated by the LabView application	-
-											-
-	- saveData.m									-
-		reads "data" and saves its content at "directory" in multiple .txt  	-
-		size and tries to find the probable real data				-
-											-
-	- filterData.m									-
-		Delete data above a limit, divide into small sets of "timeScale"	-
-   		tries to find the probable real data and saves new data in "outFile"	-
-											-
-	- filterFiles.m									-
-		Applies "filterData.m" to a set of desired files at "pathIn"		-
-   		and saves the output files at "pathOut"					-
-											-
-	- getSysInfo.m									-
-		Loads all the chracteristic values of the system			-
-											-
-	- getAirLosses.m								-
-		Calculates air loss							-
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-	-> Subfunctions:								-
-											-
-	- arrangeData.m									-
-		Arrange data into block for "separateData.m" function. Takes from 	-
-		"data" array and select only data between "h1" and "h2" indexes		-
-											-
-	- findSeries.m									-
-		Tries to detect the real direct bursts on "data", according to		-
-		the theoretical antenna turning time of "timeGap" and taking a into	-
-		account a deviation of "timeDeviation", saving the results in the	-
-   		"indexes" matrix							-
-											-
-	- getHighestValues.m								-
-		Gets highest value compared to its neighboring values			-
-   		[MUST ONLY BE USED AFTER FINDING THE REAL SERIES] 			-
-											-
-	- gsec.m									-
-		Simple script to get time as seconds					-
-											-
-	- joinData.m									-
-		Select data from "data" array using a selection vector			-
-											-
-	- myCell2Mat.m									-
-		Creates array of numbers from cell of strings representing numbers	-
-   		(either with decimal point or comma) 					-
-											-
-	- readOneFile.m									-
-		Read data from a file generated by the LabView application		-
-											-
-	- saveOneFile.m									-
-		reads "data" and saves its content at "directory" in a .txt file	-
-   		called "name"								-
-											-
-	- selectData.m									-
-		Select data from "data" array using a selection vector			-
-											-
-	- separatedata.m								-
-		Separate data into blocks accoarding to desired time window		-
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-	-> Other Files:									-
-											-
-	- systemCharacteristics.txt							-
-		Keeps system characteristics (data order MUST NOT BE CHANGED)		-
